[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772767903357,"sessionID":"ses_33ecf0becffesomNpVZnDBlJSX","part":{"id":"prt_cc13362b4001w6gh9L2TaHVnK8","sessionID":"ses_33ecf0becffesomNpVZnDBlJSX","messageID":"msg_cc1335f70001XYD9dVQERmg7o1","type":"text","text":"Built a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.tsx:1` using only local/JLCPCB-imported parts, with `routingDisabled` set on the board and a straightforward breakout layout around the RP2040, USB-C receptacle, power decoupling, reset pull-up, and a GPIO25 status LED.\n\n- Used imported JLCPCB components for the MCU, USB connector, and LED in `imports/RP2040.tsx:1`, `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx:1`, and `imports/XL_1608UGC_06A.tsx:1`\n- Exposed the RP2040 on two 1x20 header rows in `index.tsx:9` and `index.tsx:41`, including power, SWD, USB D+/D-, ADC rail, and all GPIOs\n- Wired USB-C VBUS, GND, CC pins, shield tabs, and D+/D- into the RP2040 in `index.tsx:155`, then tied the RP2040 supply-related pins to `VBUS` and `V3_3` nets with local decoupling in `index.tsx:172`\n- Added a minimal activity LED path from `GPIO25` through `R1` into `D1` in `index.tsx:197`, plus a `RUN` pull-up resistor in `index.tsx:194`\n- Assumed a minimal demonstrator breakout rather than a production-ready Pico-class design, so it omits the external QSPI flash, crystal, regulator refinement, and USB protection typically required for a fully bootable RP2040 board\n\nArtifacts were generated successfully:\n- Site build output: `dist/index.html` and `dist/index/circuit.json`\n- Snapshot output: `__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg` and `__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg`\n\nBuild notes:\n- Ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript` successfully\n- Ran `tsci snapshot` successfully\n- The build completed with a few tscircuit trace warnings around generic passive pin naming, but the output artifacts were still produced successfully","time":{"start":1772767903355,"end":1772767903355}}}

